===============================
PART 4 — CREATE WINDOWS EC2 INSTANCE
===============================
1) Go to AWS Console.
2) Click Services (top left).
3) Click EC2.
4) Click Launch Instance.
--------------------------------
Step 1 — Name the Instance
--------------------------------
In the "Name" field type:
Windows-Server
--------------------------------
Step 2 — Choose AMI
--------------------------------
Under Application and OS Images:
Select:
Microsoft Windows Server 2022 Base
--------------------------------
Step 3 — Choose Instance Type
--------------------------------
Under Instance type:
Select:
t2.micro
--------------------------------
Step 4 — Key Pair
--------------------------------
Under Key pair:
Select existing key pair:
mykey
(Do NOT create new unless required.)
--------------------------------
Step 5 — Configure Network
--------------------------------
In Network settings section:
Click Edit.
Ensure:
Auto-assign Public IP → Enabled
Under Security Group:
Enable:
Allow RDP traffic
Verify:
Port: 3389
Source: My IP
--------------------------------
Step 6 — Launch Instance
--------------------------------
Click Launch Instance.
Wait 3–5 minutes.
Go to:
EC2 → Instances
Wait until:
Instance state → Running
Status checks → 2/2 passed
===============================
PART 5 — CONNECT TO WINDOWS USING RDP
===============================
--------------------------------
Step 1 — Get Administrator Password
--------------------------------
1) Go to EC2 → Instances.
2) Select Windows-Server.
3) Click Connect.
4) Select RDP Client tab.
5) Click Get Password.
6) Click Upload private key file.
7) Upload: mykey.pem
8) Click Decrypt Password.
9) Copy the displayed password.
--------------------------------
Step 2 — Open Remote Desktop
--------------------------------
On your Windows computer:
1) Press Windows + R
2) Type: mstsc
3) Press Enter
--------------------------------
Step 3 — Login
--------------------------------
In the Remote Desktop window:
Computer:
<Public-IP-of-Windows-instance>
Click Connect.
Username:
Administrator
Password:
Paste the decrypted password.
Click OK.
--------------------------------
Windows Desktop opens.
RDP Connection Successful.
